    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://github.com/yairEO/tagify/releases/tag/v4.35.0"/>
    <title>v4.35.0</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;refactor: simplify isNodeTag function for improved readability  &lt;a class=&quot;commit-link&quot; data-hovercard-type=&quot;commit&quot; data-hovercard-url=&quot;https://github.com/yairEO/tagify/commit/5f1c50d49091b9f0bd3065c213b62d453f6be291/hovercard&quot; href=&quot;https://github.com/yairEO/tagify/commit/5f1c50d49091b9f0bd3065c213b62d453f6be291&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;5f1c50d&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;fixed &lt;code&gt;readonly&lt;/code&gt; &amp;amp; &lt;code&gt;disabled&lt;/code&gt; so it is now impossible to interact with the Tagify component when these states are set. It was previously possible to edit things when tabbing &quot;into&quot; them  &lt;a class=&quot;commit-link&quot; data-hovercard-type=&quot;commit&quot; data-hovercard-url=&quot;https://github.com/yairEO/tagify/commit/704b3b7be65ad5d96b150660a0c128a6bc86f2d1/hovercard&quot; href=&quot;https://github.com/yairEO/tagify/commit/704b3b7be65ad5d96b150660a0c128a6bc86f2d1&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;704b3b7&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;refactor: remove unnecessary &lt;code&gt;data-can-editable&lt;/code&gt; attribute from tag template  &lt;a class=&quot;commit-link&quot; data-hovercard-type=&quot;commit&quot; data-hovercard-url=&quot;https://github.com/yairEO/tagify/commit/1290deec41adaec6ded13211b1837f161de9c052/hovercard&quot; href=&quot;https://github.com/yairEO/tagify/commit/1290deec41adaec6ded13211b1837f161de9c052&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;1290dee&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;undid last change. the user should control this from the outside.  &lt;a class=&quot;commit-link&quot; data-hovercard-type=&quot;commit&quot; data-hovercard-url=&quot;https://github.com/yairEO/tagify/commit/fbd51e6063a42bc26436926a59874680ab8708c9/hovercard&quot; href=&quot;https://github.com/yairEO/tagify/commit/fbd51e6063a42bc26436926a59874680ab8708c9&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;fbd51e6&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;fix: if &lt;code&gt;userInput&lt;/code&gt; is false, only set &lt;code&gt;dropdown.enabled = 0&lt;/code&gt; if &lt;code&gt;dropdown.enabled&lt;/code&gt; setting was not intentionally set to &lt;code&gt;false/null/undefined&lt;/code&gt;, which indicates the user does not want to show it no matter what  &lt;a class=&quot;commit-link&quot; data-hovercard-type=&quot;commit&quot; data-hovercard-url=&quot;https://github.com/yairEO/tagify/commit/4fb23312a5075886142597e5e00ce39d777ba6e7/hovercard&quot; href=&quot;https://github.com/yairEO/tagify/commit/4fb23312a5075886142597e5e00ce39d777ba6e7&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;4fb2331&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;refactor: update contenteditable attributes to use data-can-editable so &quot;setContentEditable&quot; method could work properly regardless of the contenteditable attribute existance  &lt;a class=&quot;commit-link&quot; data-hovercard-type=&quot;commit&quot; data-hovercard-url=&quot;https://github.com/yairEO/tagify/commit/ced54328a3bcbf145651deb92a5a9a9d5e0894c3/hovercard&quot; href=&quot;https://github.com/yairEO/tagify/commit/ced54328a3bcbf145651deb92a5a9a9d5e0894c3&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;ced5432&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;disabled tagify with a placeholder should still show the placeholder text, but only if there are no tags  &lt;a class=&quot;commit-link&quot; data-hovercard-type=&quot;commit&quot; data-hovercard-url=&quot;https://github.com/yairEO/tagify/commit/c69ec4d49d49cfcaa264a9ed3688a67e80d4a773/hovercard&quot; href=&quot;https://github.com/yairEO/tagify/commit/c69ec4d49d49cfcaa264a9ed3688a67e80d4a773&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;c69ec4d&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
